Package data.math.definitions

Interface TransitionFunction

All Superinterfaces:
Function<BinaryTuple<State,Symbol>,State>, Relation<BinaryTuple<State,Symbol>,State>
public interface TransitionFunction extends Function<BinaryTuple<State,Symbol>,State>
A special case of a function which assigns states to tuples of one state and one symbol. The returned tuple set of this function contains tuples of the form ((state,symbol),state). Objects of this type can be used in a DFA.
